   Independently of the genetic structure of the animal material the high environmental temperature had the following effects:  1.  Body weight was reduced by 13.6 % on an average associated with a narrowing of the breast angle by 11.3 % as well as a non-significant reduction in shank length.
   2.  The average egg weight was reduced by 12 %, number of eggs by 19.5 % and egg mass by 28.8 %.
